CatDescriptText: Mrs. Agnes Lewis, 11 Alpine Avenue, North Side, was part of the "Pittsburghers Speak Up" column published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, August 16, 1958, pg. 3 with question: "Do you think that Negroes are giving sufficient financial help to the National Association for the Advancement of Colored People?" answer reads: "It is hard to say because in Pittsburgh they don't have that many drives. If there were more drives you could find out what Negroes are giving."
